  "prompt": "Are there legal obligations for financial institutions regarding money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, financial institutions have significant legal obligations regarding anti-money laundering (AML) efforts. These include:\n\n1. Regulatory Requirements\n- Implementing comprehensive AML programs\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n- Conducting customer due diligence\n- Maintaining transaction records\n- Screening customers against watchlists\n\n2. Key Laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act of 2020\n\n3. Compliance Obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Risk assessment\n- Independent audits\n- Staff training\n- Reporting large cash transactions\n\n4. Potential Consequences\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Loss of banking licenses\n- Reputational damage\n\n5. Reporting Requirements\n- Filing Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Reporting transactions over $10,000\n- Monitoring and investigating unusual activity\n\nThese obligations aim to prevent financial crimes and help law enforcement track potential illegal activities.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
